{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"44442c45-39ce-434e-9b19-1b4504f54abb","content":"**What happened:** Microsoft.Testing.Platform defaults `--minimum-expected-tests` to `1`, so assemblies with zero discovered tests exit with code 8 (\"no tests ran\"). VSTest had no such guard.\n\n**The fix:** Setting `<TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments>--minimum-expected-tests 0</TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments>` tells the runner that finding zero tests is acceptable, restoring the VSTest behavior.\n\nIf you have a `Directory.Build.props` shared across multiple test projects, you can put this property there instead to apply it solution-wide.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d3b853f4-707d-4f36-ba3b-70cd4b9fcf83","outputTokens":137,"requestId":"E3DE:165513:167854B:191A583:6A05209E"},"id":"a0d26e7a-aebf-4c92-a657-10e649fd5909","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:08:50.952Z","parentId":"3e068d6a-79d1-4d69-9f14-51c4cbfc6a22"}
